Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a formal approach to learning and planning for agents operating in unknown environments, which is a common topic in AI research. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a method for computing the maximally likely model of the environment, which involves statistical inference and estimation. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the proposed method can be applied to control policies for time-varying Markov decision processes, which is relevant to robotics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with modeling and controlling time-varying systems. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a less likely category, but still possible as the proposed method can be applied to agents operating in unknown environments, which is relevant to multiagent systems.
